Firstly; I got whipped vigorously all over my body with a bunch of plants and herbs infused in alcohol; then I had a un-cracked egg rubbed over my head and body and once cracked she “looked” at the inside of the egg and told me I’m holding onto many nerves (unsurprising).
Then I had alcohol sprayed onto my hands and I had to breathe it in (it was pretty potent); to them see her spray some in her mouth and spit (yes; that’s right; SPIT) it on m belly.
Then lastly she spit onto a tub of what looked like black powder and rubbed it onto my belly button (that was a bit unpleasant); the bottom of my back and my forehead in the shape of a cross.

This is meant to cleanse (as the name limpia translates to) and it’s meant to help get rid of any terrible from within. Just one of the many cultural and interesting things to experience/do in Cuenca!
